JOHANNESBURG – Former President Jacob Zuma's son has died. Zuma's spokesperson Vukile Mathabela confirmed that Vusi Nhlakanipho Zuma has died, but could not provide further details. “Yes, I can confirm that Vusi [Nhlakanipho Zuma] passed on.” The ANC released a statement, saying it is deeply saddened by his untimely passing. "A bright and promising young lion and disciplined member of the ANC, Nhlakanipho Zuma was a dedicated and a humble activist who took a keen interest in the livelihoods of our people," read the statement. "His acts of kindness and gentle soul will forever remain in our hearts." He was 25-years-old and was the youngest of children born to Zuma and the late Kate Zuma. His siblings are Duduzile and Duduzane Zuma. eNCA